Filters in Insight Builder

The filters in the Visual builder are similar to the “Where” clause in the standard SQL. You can define filters on the measures and dimensions.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
In the visual builder screen, select the Demo DMO as the object.
Select the filter node by clicking the + icon.
In the Measures tab, select the SUM function and select the measure (Quantity) on which aggregate must be applied. Select the dimension (Product ID) to group By.
Apply the aggregate.
Select the next node as Filter.
EXAMPLE

To create a filter expression from the visual builder, consider the demo DMO. Consider a scenario where the user wants to have products for which more than 100 units are ordered.

ORDERID	PRODUCTID	QUANTITY
13131	3131	23
In the visual builder screen, select the Demo DMO as the object.
Select the filter node by clicking the + icon.
In the Measures tab, select the SUM function and select the measure (Quantity) on which aggregate must be applied.
Select the dimension (Product ID) to group By.
Apply the aggregate.
Now select the next node as Filter.
In the Take Action When dropdown, select the “All Conditions Are Met”.
To create the filtering condition, click the + icon to create the filtering condition.
Select the newly created field, Total Quantity, and click Next.
Select the Operator as “greater than” and add the value as 100.
Apply the Filter and save.

The CI builder returns are equivalent to the following expression:

SELECT ProductID, SUM(Quantity) as Total Quantity 
FROM OrderDetails
WHERE Total Quantity > 100
Group by ProductID
